### ── TEST DRIVE SERVICE (/test-drive) ──────────────────────────────────────
### Environment: Ctrl+Shift+P → Rest Client: Switch Environment → dev

### 1. Get available slots — Golf VIII, München, future date
GET {{baseUrl}}/test-drive/getAvailableSlots(vehicleId='40000000-4000-4000-4000-400000000001',branchId='aaa00000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',date='2026-07-10')

### 2. Request test drive — Customer Bauer, Golf VIII
# @name createTD
POST {{baseUrl}}/test-drive/requestTestDrive
Authorization: {{customerBauerAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vehicleId": "40000000-4000-4000-4000-400000000001",
  "branchId": "aaa00000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "scheduledAt": "2026-07-10T09:00:00Z",
  "notes": "Ich möchte das Fahrzeug auf der Autobahn testen"
}

### 3. List test drives — Operator
GET {{baseUrl}}/test-drive/TestDrives
Authorization: {{operatorAuth}}

### 4. Approve test drive — Operator
### testDriveId: replace with ID returned from step 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/test-drive/approveTestDrive
Authorization: {{operatorAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "testDriveId": "REPLACE_WITH_ID",
  "scheduledAt": "2026-07-10T09:00:00Z"
}

### 5. Complete test drive — Operator
POST {{baseUrl}}/test-drive/completeTestDrive
Authorization: {{operatorAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "testDriveId": "REPLACE_WITH_ID"
}

### 6. Cancel test drive — Customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/test-drive/cancelTestDrive
Authorization: {{customerBauerAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "testDriveId": "REPLACE_WITH_ID"
}

### 7. Guest test drive request — no authentication required
POST {{baseUrl}}/test-drive/requestTestDriveAsGuest
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vehicleId": "40000000-4000-4000-4000-400000000006",
  "branchId": "aaa00000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "scheduledAt": "2026-07-15T10:00:00Z",
  "contactEmail": "gast@beispiel.de",
  "contactPhone": "+49 89 555 0000",
  "notes": "Interesse am Tiguan"
}
